This yegr the State’s tourist map calls special attention to Maryland’s western coun-
ties which form one of the nation’s most attractive and exciting mountain playgrounds.

The region is known for its glorious vistas visible from Maryland’s modern high-
ways which run along tree-lined mountain tops.

Western Maryland is a year-round vacation paradise. In the summer, there is swim-
ming, fishing and boating in pine-rimmed fresh water lakes; in the fall, hillsides burst
into many colors as the leaves turn with the changing season; in the winter the moun-
tains are covered with snow, making the region a mecca for ski enthusiasts.

Other recreational facilities abound throughout the region. There are sporty golf
courses, nature trails, and the Department of Forests and Parks maintains acres of
beautiful camp sites.

In addition, there are a great number of fine places for lodging and dining
throughout the Western Maryland region.

While recreation is an important phase of Western Maryland life, the region plays
its part in contributing to the industrial and economic strength of our nation. Many
important industrial establishments are located in Western Maryland.

'The counties of the western part of the State are rich in history. Much of the Civil
War unfolded in the area and key developments in the evolution ofomencu as a
great industrial power occurred in Western Marylond
